715461f-b.title: Manhattan: 126th Street (West) - Old Broadway
715461f-b.text:
(1)
St. Mary's Protestant Episcopal Church, 521 West 126th Street,
north side, between Old Broadway and Amsterdam Avenue. The house
in the rear of the church is a 22-story frame house which is
evidently used as the parsonage.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 350.
(2)
Tablet on the wall of St. Mary's Protestant Episcopal Church.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 351.

715456f-a.title: Manhattan: 126th Street (West) - Old Broadway
715456f-a.text:
V. 126th (formerly Lawrence) Street, south side, east
from a point midwav betweenn Old Broadway and Amsterdam Avenue
and towards the latter (extremme left and not seen). Shown is
a vacant lot, a 4 story framme house, the Spever School and
several low structures. These buildings forrerly were known
as No's. 98 to 88 Lawrence Street but now bear No's. 518 to
498 . 126th Street. St. Marys P.E. Chumrch is on the side wNere
the photogranher is standing and therefor does not appear. In
fact the vacant lot shown is directly opnosite same.
April 1, 1938.
P.L. Sperr
